      "id": "section-01",
      "number": 1,
      "numberStr": "01",
      "key": "MISH_01",
      "title": "Safety Health Program Overview",
      "slug": "safety-health-program-overview",
      "previewHtml": "<h1>1.0 PURPOSE &amp; SCOPE</h1><p><strong>1.1 </strong>MH Construction, Inc. is committed to providing a safe and healthful work environment for all employees, subcontractors, and visitors on every project.</p><p><strong>1.2 </strong>This Safety &amp; Health Program applies to all MHC operations, including commercial construction, remodel, restoration, and government contracts in Washington State.</p><p><strong>1.3 </strong>This program is aligned with the AGC Construction Safety Excellence Awards (CSEA) framework, OSHA 29 CFR 1926, WAC 296-155 (WISHA), and Travelers Risk Control best practices.</p>"
    },
    {
