    {
      "id": "section-34",
      "number": 34,
      "numberStr": "34",
      "key": "MISH_34",
      "title": "Distracted Driving Mobile Device Policy",
      "slug": "distracted-driving-mobile-device-policy",
      "previewHtml": "<h1>1.0 PURPOSE &amp; SCOPE</h1><p><strong>1.1 </strong>This policy establishes MH Construction's requirements for the safe use of mobile technology devices while operating any vehicle on behalf of the company.</p><p><strong>1.2 </strong>This policy applies to all employees, subcontractors, and agents who operate company-owned, rented, leased, borrowed, or personally-owned vehicles for MHC business.</p><p><strong>1.3 </strong>Mobile technology devices include: cellular phones, smartphones, tablets, laptops, GPS/navigation systems, portable audio/video players, and any other electronic device.</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "section-35",
      "number": 35,
      "numberStr": "35",
      "key": "MISH_35",
      "title": "Motor Vehicle Records Program",
      "slug": "motor-vehicle-records-program",
      "previewHtml": "<h1>1.0 PURPOSE &amp; SCOPE</h1><p><strong>1.1 </strong>MH Construction requires Motor Vehicle Record (MVR) checks for all employees who operate vehicles on behalf of the company, including company-owned, rented, leased, borrowed, or personally-owned vehicles.</p><p><strong>1.2 </strong>MVR reviews help identify drivers with poor driving histories before incidents occur, reducing liability and protecting employees and the public.</p><p><strong>1.3 </strong>This program applies to all MHC employees, including supervisors, project managers, and field personnel who drive on MHC business.</p>"
    },
